# .trivyignore — accepted risks with no fix available
#
# Each entry is reviewed and documented. Re-evaluate when:
# - upstream releases a patched binary (yq, gh)
# - Debian bookworm security team backports a fix
#
# Format: CVE-ID [expiry-date] # comment

# ── Go stdlib CVEs in yq and gh ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# yq v4.53.2 is the current latest; gh is from Debian apt.
# Both are affected by Go stdlib CVEs that require the upstream maintainer to
# rebuild with a patched Go toolchain. No fix is available in either binary
# as of 2026-05-16. Re-check when yq > v4.53.2 or gh > 2.72.0 ships.
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39823
CVE-2026-39825
CVE-2026-39826
CVE-2026-39836
CVE-2026-42499
# github.com/in-toto/in-toto-golang bundled in gh binary; no patched gh release yet
GHSA-pmwq-pjrm-6p5r

# ── @modelcontextprotocol/sdk in MCP npm cache ───────────────────────────────
# server-github 2025.4.8 is the current latest; the sdk CVEs require the MCP
# team to release a new server version. Accepted until a patched release ships.
CVE-2025-66414
CVE-2026-0621

# ── System npm packages (Node.js bundled npm deps) ───────────────────────────
# picomatch, ip-address, brace-expansion are transitive deps of npm itself.
# Fixing requires a Node.js version that ships updated bundled npm deps — not
# something we control. Risk: npm-internal tooling only, not user-facing code.
CVE-2026-33671
CVE-2026-33672
CVE-2026-42338
CVE-2026-33750

# ── pip CVEs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# pip is installed by the uv base image. These CVEs affect pip's download/install
# behavior — not exploitable in our read-only production image where pip is not
# invoked at runtime (uv handles all installs at build time).
CVE-2025-8869
CVE-2026-6357
CVE-2026-3219
CVE-2026-1703

# ── Long-standing Debian bookworm CVEs with no backport ──────────────────────
# These have been open in Debian bookworm for 2+ years with no security
# backport scheduled. The packages are required runtime deps (ffmpeg, tesseract,
# poppler-utils). Removing them would break core Hermes Agent capabilities.

# libaom3 — AV1 codec used by ffmpeg; no Debian bookworm fix for either CVE
CVE-2023-39616
CVE-2023-6879

# libmfx1 — Intel Media SDK acceleration for ffmpeg; no Debian bookworm fix
CVE-2023-45221

# zlib1g — compression library; no Debian bookworm fix for this variant
CVE-2023-45853

# libharfbuzz0b — text shaping; no Debian bookworm fix
CVE-2023-25193

# libldap-2.5-0 — LDAP client library; no Debian bookworm fix
CVE-2023-2953
